genresAdvancedInfo.name: indorock
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Indorock is a genre of music that emerged in Indonesia in the 1960s. It is a fusion of traditional Indonesian music and Western rock and roll. Indorock is characterized by its use of electric guitars, drums, and bass, as well as traditional Indonesian instruments like the kecapi and suling.
